1 (c) A person at least eighteen (18) years of age who knowingly or
2 intentionally:
3 (1) knowingly or intentionally communicates with an individual
4 whom the person believes to be a child less than fourteen (14)
5 years of age concerning sexual activity with the intent to gratify
6 the sexual desires of the person or the individual; or
7 (2) engages in a pattern of repeated or continuous contact
8 with an individual whom the person believes to be a child less
9 than fourteen (14) years of age with the intent to make the
10 individual less resistant to future sexual conduct;
11 commits inappropriate communication with a child sexual grooming,
12 a Class B misdemeanor. However, the offense is:
13 (1) a Class A misdemeanor if the person commits the offense by
14 using a computer network (as defined in IC 35-43-2-3(a); and
15 (2) a Level 6 felony if the person has a prior unrelated conviction
16 for a sex offense (as defined in IC 11-8-8-5.2).
