19 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 14. (a) As used in this section, "serious sex
20 offender" means a person required to register as a sex offender under
21 IC 11-8-8 who is:
22 (1) found to be a sexually violent predator under IC 35-38-1-7.5;
23 or
24 (2) convicted of one (1) or more of the following offenses:
25 (A) Child molesting (IC 35-42-4-3).
26 (B) Child exploitation (IC 35-42-4-4(b) or IC 35-42-4-4(c)).
27 (C) Possession of child sex abuse material (IC 35-42-4-4(d) or
28 IC 35-42-4-4(e)).
29 (D) Vicarious sexual gratification (IC 35-42-4-5(a) and
30 IC 35-42-4-5(b)).
31 (E) Performing sexual conduct in the presence of a minor
32 (IC 35-42-4-5(c)).
33 (F) Child solicitation (IC 35-42-4-6).
34 (G) Child seduction (IC 35-42-4-7).
35 (H) Sexual misconduct with a minor (IC 35-42-4-9).
36 (b) A serious sex offender who knowingly or intentionally enters:
37 (1) school property; or
38 (2) a:
39 (A) facility; or
40 (B) location holding an event;
41 that provides entertainment or programming primarily
42 directed toward a child less than eighteen (18) years of age;
